PRACTICAL 7: Using Templates and Clones
Prerequisites

• Practical 6 completed
• Virtual machine installed and configured

Steps

Create a new virtual machine with required OS.

Install OS updates and VMware Tools.

Power off the virtual machine.

Convert the virtual machine into a Template.

Create Customization Specifications for OS configuration.

Deploy a new virtual machine from the template.

Apply customization settings during deployment.

Power on the deployed virtual machine and verify configuration.

Create clones from existing virtual machines as required.
